The differences between the LM8 and the MRP CQB rifle is that the LM8 does not have the Picatinny rails machined into the upper. title: For Sale/Trade:  Blueprinted Rem 700 .300 WSM
postcontent:
For your consideration is a blueprinted Remington 700 chambered in .300 Winchester Short Magnum. The short mag action has been squared and trued center to bore; the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore. The actions lugs have also been squared and trued. The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared. All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore. Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed.

A brand new Shilen, match grade, chrome barrel was used for this build. The contour is a #5 contour (heavy sporter but not quite a varmint), 10 twist and finished at 24". The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action. The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015". This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter. The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown. The barrel has only 3 rounds through her... I have plenty of pics to share showing the machine work being completed.

Once the machine work was completed and the rifle test fired the barreled action was caustic blued but can always be customized to your needs...  Maybe add a muzzle brake; cerakote finish; detachable mag; Jewell trigger, ect.

The barreled action in a quality stock will easily shoot 3/4 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/2 MOA or better using hand loaded ammo. I have a few HS precision stocks and a few Bell and Carlson stocks to offer with this build...

The .300 WSM is stocked in a Bell and Carlson sporter stock and can be swapped into an HS precision if preferred.  I have plenty of more pics if needed.  If you prefer just the barreled action - I can offer just the barreled action for 1100.  

I have a few other blueprinted Rem 700s available as well so if you have another caliber in mind send a note... I probably have it or can build it.

Make a fair offer - the worst I can say is no thanks...  Will ship to your FFL if needed.
